narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: This class works well to make you feel comfortable being to read, understand, and express your ideas in Greek. While L1 is largely just foundational, in this course Maria is able to get you to a point where you feel comfortable reading basic passages, asking questions to native speakers, and talking about your interactions with everyday things.
L2 Greek, grammar and vocabulary. I feel like my Greek skills really took off this semester!

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The pace could have been slowed down a little at the end but other than that it was great!

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I absolutely would recommend this course to another interested in studying Greek. The language is not the easiest you can choose, but the culture is fascinating and Maria does a fantastic job of immersing you in Greek. If you have an interest in the Greek language, this course is everything you would hope for it to be.
Best course/professor I've ever had. Maria is so helpful, always willing to work with you if you miss a class/don't understand a concept.
Yes. I learned a lot and enjoyed the class very much.
